BFN 

<F P=106> [By Lo Kuang-jen and Debbie Kuo] </F>
  [Text] Los Angeles, May 29 (CNA) -- Premier Lien Chan 
arrived in Los Angeles Sunday [29 May] afternoon for an 
overnight stay on his way to Central America for a state visit. 
  Lien was met at the airport by Natale Bellocchi, managing 
director of the American Institute in Taiwan (AIT), the 
unofficial conduit for U.S.-Taiwan ties. 
  Also on hand to meet Lien and his 21-member entourage was 
ROC 
representative to the U.S. Ding Mou-shih. 
  The premier and his party will fly to Miami Monday where 
they 
will spend the night before proceeding to El Salvador. Lien 
will represent President Li Teng-hui at the inauguration of El 
Salvadoran President-elect Armando Calderon Sol June 1. 
  Lien is expected to meet with his old friends in El 
Salvador, 
where he served as ROC ambassador in 1975-1976. 
  Lien will travel to Guatemala on June 2 for a four-day state 
visit. 
  This will be Lien's second state visit overseas since 
January. 
  During his time in Guatemala, Lien will discuss issues of 
mutual concern with Guatemalan President Ramiro de Leon Carpio. 
  Lien is traveling with his wife, Vice Foreign Affairs 
Minister Fang Chin-yen and his wife, ROC Ambassador to El 
Salvador Shen Jen- piao, Government Information Office 
Director-General Jason Hu, Council of Agriculture Chairman Sun 
Ming-hsien, and Central Bank of China Deputy Director Yu Chen. 

